list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Remove IDEA project files and add manifest for Snake extension
Deleted IntelliJ IDEA's project-specific configuration files to exclude unnecessary metadata from version control. Added a `manifest.json` file to define the basic structure and metadata for the Snake browser extension. This improves project organization and prepares it for extension deployment.

task.summary:
Add game loop and refactor canvas and snake logic
Introduced a `main` game loop for continuous updates and refactored canvas initialization and snake movement functions for better modularity. Removed redundant canvas setup logic and encapsulated it into reusable functions. These changes improve code readability and maintainability.

Add game logic to implement Snake functionality
Introduced core game mechanics including snake movement, food generation, scoring, and collision detection. Refactored code for clarity, added constants for configuration, and set up event listeners for user input handling.

Add README.md with project description and tutorial link
This README file provides an overview of the Snake web game. It includes a link to the tutorial used for building the game, offering context and guidance for future reference.

Add score display to snake game UI
Introduced a score heading and placeholder to the game interface. This sets up the foundation for displaying and updating the player's score dynamically in future updates.
